This paper discusses machine learning algorithms and their application in algorithmic fairness. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on three classical machine learning algorithms. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CY (Computers and Society), as the paper discusses the ethical implications of algorithmic fairness. Additionally, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) may be relevant as the paper addresses discrimination and bias in algorithms.
